  "response": "There are many legal precedents related to money laundering cases across different jurisdictions. Some key examples include:\n\n1. United States v. BCCI (1991)\n- Landmark case involving extensive international money laundering\n- Resulted in significant banking regulations\n\n2. United States v. HSBC (2012)\n- Major case involving international money laundering sanctions\n- HSBC paid $1.9 billion in penalties\n\n3. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Revealed complex international money laundering networks\n- Led to significant reforms in banking oversight\n\n4. United States v. Liberty Reserve (2013)\n- Major digital currency money laundering prosecution\n- Demonstrated legal approaches to cryptocurrency-based laundering\n\n5. United States v. Santos (2008)\n- Supreme Court clarification of money laundering statutes\n- Defined interpretation of proceeds in criminal proceedings\n\nThese cases have established important legal principles regarding:\n- Identifying laundering activities\n- Proving intentional financial concealment\n- Prosecuting complex financial crimes\n- Establishing international cooperation in investigations\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal precedents?",
